Description: This takes spatial single-cell-type RNA-seq data (specifically designed for Slide-seq v2) that calls copy number alterations ('CNAs') using 'pseudo-spatial' binning, clusters cellular units (e.g. beads) based on 'CNA' profile, and visualizes spatial 'CNA' patterns.
